      "raw_text": "ST. PAUL, March 14.-Notice\nthat railroad rates will be raised\nwas served yesterday by j. J. Hill\non the state senate committee\nwhich Is Investigating state rail\nroad affairs. In the course of his\nargument he claimed that the\nGreat Northern made the lowest\nrates In the country and the same\nrates, If put in effect on the Union\nPacific, would decrease the earn.\nings of that line $5,000,O00 In.\ncreased rates must come, he said\nto save many roads from\nbankruptcy."
